{"atom_id":"ig34_p0324_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":324,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined reference number. May be preprinted on the CRF as an explicit line identifier or defined in the sponsor's operational database. Example: Question number on a questionnaire. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0324_a017","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":324,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSTESTCD | Question Short Name | Char | * | Topic | Topic variable for QS. Short name for the value in QSTEST, which can be used as a column name when converting the dataset from a vertical format to a horizontal format. The value in QSTESTCD cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"1TEST\" is not valid). QSTESTCD cannot contain characters other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Controlled terminology for QSTESTCD is published in separate codelists for each questionnaire. See https://www.cdisc.org/standards/semantics/terminology for values for QSTESTCD. Examples: \"ADCCMD01\", \"BPR0103\". | Req |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":["https://www.cdisc.org/standards/semantics/terminology"],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0324_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":324,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSTEST | Question Name | Char | * | Synonym Qualifier | Verbatim name of the question or group of questions used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in QSTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Controlled terminology for QSTEST is published in separate codelists for each questionnaire. See https://www.cdisc.org/standards/semantics/terminology for values for QSTEST. Example: \"BPR01 - Emotional Withdrawal\". | Req |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":["https://www.cdisc.org/standards/semantics/terminology"],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0324_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":324,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSCAT | Category of Question | Char | (QSCAT) | Grouping Qualifier | Used to specify the questionnaire in which the question identified by QSTEST and QSTESTCD was included. Examples: \"ADAS-COG\", \"MDS-UPDRS\". | Req |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0324_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":324,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSSCAT | Subcategory for Question | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of the questions within the category. Examples: \"MENTAL HEALTH\" , \"DEPRESSION\", \"WORD RECALL\". | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0324_a021","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":324,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSORRES | Finding in Original Units | Char | | Result Qualifier | Finding as originally received or collected (e.g., \"RARELY\", \"SOMETIMES\"). When sponsors apply codelist to indicate that code values are statistically meaningful standardized scores (which are defined by sponsors or by valid methodologies, e.g., SF36 questionnaires), QSORRES will contain the decode format; QSSTRESC and QSSTRESN may contain the standardized code values or scores. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0325_a001","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":325,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSORRESU | Original Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Original units in which the data were collected. The unit for QSORRES, such as minutes or seconds or the units associated with a visual analog scale. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0325_a002","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":325,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the finding for all questions or subscores copied or derived from QSORRES, in a standard format or standard units. QSSTRESC should store all findings in character format; if findings are numeric, they should also be stored in numeric format in QSSTRESN. If question scores are derived from the original finding, then the standard format is the score. Examples: \"0\", \"1\". When sponsors apply codelist to indicate the code values are statistically meaningful standardized scores (which are defined by sponsors or by valid methodologies, e.g., SF36 questionnaires), QSORRES will contain the decode format; QSSTRESC and QSSTRESN may contain the standardized code values or scores. | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0325_a003","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":325,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSSTRESN | Numeric Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous or numeric findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from QSSTRESC. QSSTRESN should store all numeric results or findings. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0325_a004","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":325,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSSTRESU | Standard Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized unit used for QSSTRESC or QSSTRESN. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0325_a005","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":325,"page_region":"top","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate that a question was not done or was not answered. Should be null if a result exists in QSORRES. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
