{"atom_id":"ig34_p0325_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":325,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.9.2 Questionnaires (QS)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| QSDRVFL | Derived Flag | Char | (NY) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate a derived record. The value should be \"Y\" or null. Records that represent the average of other records or questionnaire subscores that do not come from the CRF are examples of records that would be derived for the submission datasets. If QSDRVFL = \"Y\", then QSORRES may be null with QSSTRESC and (if numeric) QSSTRESN having the derived value. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:executor","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-28T00:00:00Z"}}
